The police said they have arrested 12 suspected miscreants for stealing at the scene of a fire disaster which claimed the life of a policeman on Tuesday in Lagos Island. Speaking to newsmen on Wednesday during the evacuation of the building at 43 Martins Street, Lagos, Olubode Ojajuni, Assistant Commissioner of Police, Area “A” Command, identified the dead policeman as Sergent Michael Dominic. “We have hoodlums and miscreants who took advantage of the situation to steal and we arrested 12 people, who are now in detention,’’ Ojajuna said. ALSO READ: BREAKING: Popular Lagos Balogun Market on fire How a dying man was raised in Adamawa crusade — Bishop Zuga Don’t privatize water sector AUPCTRE, ERA/FoEN appeal… Bayelsa poll: 7 PDP govs, chairman, others storm Yenagoa Lagos fire: Sanwo-Olu visits Balogun market, sympathises… Also speaking at the scene, Director-General of LASEMA, Dr Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu, said that the emergency response team was able to put off the fire in the early hours of Wednesday. He said that Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State had visited the scene to sympathise with the affected traders. Earlier, Special Adviser to the Lagos State Governor on Central Business District, Mr Olanrewaju Elegushi, said that the governor had promised to assist the affected traders who lost goods in the inferno. Elegushi said that the cause of the fire remained unknown. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
